news.title: Fire safety survey of buildings begins in Adityapur
news.para: The additional town commissioner (ATC) of AMC, Girja Shankar Prasad, has constituted a five-member committee led by assistant town planner Payal Kumari for the work. The survey will continue till February 12 and the report will be submitted to ATC Girja.

news.title: Housing for poor gets Rs 7,890 crore share in Telangana budget 2023
news.para: The state government has allocated 7,890 crore to implement the scheme in its annual budget for 2023-24. The sop assumes significance as there is a huge gap between the demand and supply for 2-BHK houses in the state.

news.title: Nashik: 1.3 lakh properties found with extra constructions without permission
news.para: The NMC is in the process of serving notices to the owners of such properties for seeking their views on the issue. But if the civic body is not convinced with their arguments, additional property tax would be levied on such properties.

news.title: Jharkhand CM meets rural development minister; seeks nod for pending houses under PMAY
news.para: Soren said as many as 629,447 houses under the PM Awas rural scheme were pending for approval with the Union rural development ministry. Also, information on 207,775 houses was not captured on the list due to errors in data entry and hence the central government should facilitate verification and approval of these beneficiaries, he said.

news.title: Bihar RERA to conduct workshop for homebuyers' awareness
news.para: People who plan to buy a flat in any real estate project with more than eight flats, or plots with an area of more than 500 square metres are eligible to participate in the workshop.

news.title: Gurugram: No flats six years on, buyers demand action against Ocean Seven Buildtech
news.para: The affordable housing project was launched in 2017 by Ocean Seven Buildtech Pvt Limited (OSB) and the buyers were promised possession in 2021. The deadline was extended to 2023 in view of the pandemic.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh identifies sites for rental housing scheme in 27 towns
news.para: The urban development department identified sites across 27 towns in UP where dwelling units will be provided to skilled and unskilled workforce, who are forced to stay in slums or roadside shanties.

news.title: Now, track building projects on West Bengal RERA website
news.para: A state housing department official said it was mandatory for developers to register online all housing projects that will be constructed on land measuring 7.5 cottah or more.

news.title: Registries pending, Noida homebuyers to protest with postcards to President
news.para: “Despite 13 years of struggle, our problem continues. No MP, MLA or Noida Authority officials have stood with us or taken note of our protest,” said Abhishek Kumar, president of New Era Flat Owners Welfare Association (NEFOWA).

news.title: Gurugram: Green View buyers reject NBCC's second settlement offer
news.para: Earlier this month, the developer had proposed to offer the total payment of the flat by fixing the base price at Rs 5,100 per sq feet to those who purchased their homes in 2012.

news.title: Gurugram: CBI seeks Chintels Paradiso papers, IIT audit findings
news.para: Apart from project details and related approvals, including licence, occupation certificates (OC) and construction-related information, the probe agency also sought the IIT report related to the testing of samples.

news.title: MahaRERA establishes counselling set up for homebuyers, developers
news.para: Both homebuyers and developers can seek guidance of these counsellors through an in-person meeting in MahaRERA’s office in Mumbai’s Bandra-Kurla Complex (BKC).

news.title: Nuvoco Vistas posts net loss of Rs 75.29 crore in Q3 FY23
news.para: Nuvoco Vistas' consolidated total income stood at Rs 2,608.76 crore in Q3 FY23, a growth of 19.68 per cent from Rs 2,179.71 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Berger Paints' manufacturing facility in Uttar Pradesh commences operations
news.para: Berger Paints has made an investment of more than Rs 1,000 crore for setting-up the manufacturing facility which has the capability to produce 15,000 KUMT per month of water-based paint, 4,800 KL per month of solvent-based paint.

news.title: SC upholds Bombay HC order protecting residents' right to form CHS
news.para: Rusabh Shah, chief promoter of New Pushpanjali Co-operative Housing Society (proposed) in Prabhadevi, had filed a petition against developer Avarsekar & Sons in 2018. Shah had challenged a rejection of the proposed society's plea to be registered as a CHS.
